  "text": "Adult guinea pigs (Cavia porcellus) were injected intraperitoneally with cyclophosphamide according to 11 different dosing schemes, administrating 1-6 times consecutively including a couple of day break (n = 55, n = 5/ group, as in case [CITATION_1] ). The dose of cyclophosphamide was calculated according to the guinea pigs' mass using the dosage of human protocols (150 mg/kg b.m.). Untreated guinea pigs were used as controls (n = 5).",
